{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast to existing surveys of GenAI evaluation, our work focuses exclusively on red-teaming.",
    "Some of our findings resonate with points earlier made by Bockting et al. [20] and Friedler et al.",
    "[56], who argue for interdisciplinary audits of AI systems by diverse groups of people and red-teaming with concrete definitions of harms alongside other evaluations, respectively.",
    "Case Studies: AI Red-teaming in practiceTo capture the complexity involved in designing real-world AI red-teaming exercises, we synthesize the results from such exercises recently conducted with generative models as case studies.",
    "Through these case studies, we seek to understand common red-teaming practices, typical resources required for successful red-teaming, effects of red-teaming on deployed models, common pitfalls, and disclosure of results with community stakeholders.Methodology."
  ]
}